(133, 189, 9, 4, '2025-06-21', 'HW - Draw A Goose', 'Geese are large, heavy-bodied waterfowl, generally larger than ducks but smaller than swans, belonging to the family Anatidae. They are known for their webbed feet, long necks, and distinctive bills, which are often humped and narrower at the tip. Geese are primarily herbivores, feeding on grasses, plants, and seeds, though some species may also consume aquatic invertebrates.', 'uploads/homework_attachments/cdb1af34d8f8cbea_Enhanced june w1.png'),
