(146, 457, 2, 5, '2025-06-26', 'HW- Boat', '1. Boats Can Float Because of Air!\r\nEven heavy boats float because their shape pushes water aside and there\'s lots of air inside. That’s called buoyancy!\r\n\r\n2. Boats Come in All Sizes\r\nFrom tiny canoes to giant cruise ships — some boats are small enough for one person, while others are like floating cities!\r\n\r\n3. Wind-Powered Boats\r\nSailboats move using wind in their sails — no fuel needed! It’s like riding the wind on water. 🌬️⛵\r\n\r\n4. Boats Were Made Long Ago\r\nThe first boats were built over 10,000 years ago — made of logs and animal skins!', 'uploads/homework_attachments/8abcf0f3f14f6421_week 2 june.png'),
