(150, 457, 2, 5, '2025-06-29', 'HW - Lady Bug', 'Tiny Superheroes!\r\nLadybugs eat plant-eating bugs like aphids, helping farmers and gardens. They\'re tiny pest controllers in disguise!\r\n\r\nRed = “Stay Away!”\r\nTheir bright red color tells predators: “I taste yucky!” It’s their built-in warning system.\r\n\r\nThey Can Fly!\r\nHidden under those pretty red shells are wings! Ladybugs can flap their wings up to 85 times per second!\r\n\r\nNot All Are Red\r\nSome ladybugs are yellow, orange, pink, or even black with different numbers of spots.\r\n\r\nLucky Bugs!\r\nIn many cultures, seeing a ladybug is considered good luck—especially if it lands on you!', 'uploads/homework_attachments/dc9aef10f8aa34c8_ladybug color pencil week 4.png'),
