(153, 475, 2, 5, '2025-06-29', 'HW-Lady Bug', '1. They’re Not Actually Bugs!\r\nLadybugs are beetles, not true bugs — and their real name is the ladybird beetle.\r\n\r\n2. Spots Are Their Style!\r\nLadybugs can have different numbers of spots — some have no spots at all, while others have over 20!\r\n\r\n3. They’re Garden Superheroes 🦸‍♀️\r\nLadybugs love eating aphids (tiny plant-eating insects), so gardeners love ladybugs for keeping plants safe.\r\n\r\n4. They Play Dead to Stay Safe\r\nWhen scared, a ladybug might curl up and pretend to be dead, or release a stinky smell to scare off predators!', 'uploads/homework_attachments/f671751ff8b31f50_ladybug color pencil week 4.png'),
