(253, 450, 3, 2, '2025-07-08', 'HW - Print and color - Basketball', 'The boy was the shortest on his school basketball team. Everyone thought he was too small to make a difference. But he never gave up. He practiced every morning before school, from dribbling to passing to shooting, again and again.\r\n\r\nOne day, during the inter-school finals, the score was tied. Only 5 seconds remained. Their star player was blocked. With a quick pass, the ball landed in the boy’s hands. Everyone held their breath.\r\n\r\nHe didn’t think twice. He dribbled once and took the shot.\r\n\r\nThe ball soared through the air. Swish. It went right through the net.\r\n\r\nThe crowd erupted in cheers. The boy had won the game. That day, he proved that being small doesn’t mean you can’t do something big.', 'uploads/homework/1751974894_basketball.png'),
(254, 204, 3, 4, '2025-07-08', 'HW - Draw and color - badminton', 'I fly without wings, have feathers but am not a bird. You hit me back and forth until I fall.\r\n→ (What am I? Shuttlecock)\r\n\r\nI’m held in your hand, light and fast, used to smash and serve really fast.\r\n→ (What am I? Badminton racket)\r\n\r\nTwo players or four, a net in the middle. I’m the game where quick feet and sharp eyes win.\r\n→ (What game am I? Badminton)\r\n\r\nI’m gentle, but tricky. I barely cross the net and fall like a feather.\r\n→ (What shot am I? Drop shot)\r\n\r\nI move fast in the air, but I’m not a bullet. Players chase me with rackets.\r\n→ (What am I? Shuttlecock)', 'uploads/homework/1751975021_bATMINTION.png'),
