(264, 194, 3, 8, '2025-07-08', 'HW - Draw and shade.', 'Homework 1 – Full Portrait (For Advanced Students)\r\nTopic: Capture the Expression – Girl’s Portrait\r\n\r\n\r\n Homework 2 – Facial Features Practice (For Beginners)\r\nTopic: Practice Drawing Individual Features\r\n\r\nDraw 4 sets of eyes (with different shapes or emotions).\r\n\r\nDraw 2–3 types of noses — front view and side view.\r\n\r\nDraw 3 kinds of lips — smiling, neutral, sad.\r\n\r\n✏️ Focus on proportions, shading, and symmetry. Use light pencil work for neatness.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDraw a full portrait of a girl showing any one expression: sad / happy / thinking / curious.\r\n\r\nFocus on the eyes, lips, and overall mood of the face.\r\n\r\nUse light and shadow to show emotion.\r\n\r\n📝 Try to tell a story through the face — even without words.', 'uploads/homework/1751975453_hw.pdf'),
