(144, 170, 'New Homework Assigned', 'You have a new homework assignment:\n“APJ ABDUL KALAM”\n1. Missile Man of India\r\nDr. Kalam played a key role in developing India’s missile programs, especially Agni and Prithvi. His work in DRDO and ISRO earned him the nickname “Missile Man of India.”\r\n\r\n2. Visionary President (2002–2007)\r\nAs the 11th President of India, Kalam was known as the “People’s President.” He inspired millions with his humility, accessibility, and forward-thinking vision for India’s future.\r\n\r\n3. Architect of Pokhran-II Nuclear Tests\r\nHe was the chief scientific advisor behind India\'s 1998 nuclear tests. This established India as a nuclear power and made him a national icon.\r\n\r\n4. A Teacher at Heart\r\nDespite his fame, Kalam always identified himself as a teacher first. He spent his final moments delivering a lecture to students at IIM Shillong in 2015. His message: “Dream, dream, dream. Dreams transform into thoughts and thoughts result in action.”\r\n\r\n5. Author & Youth Icon\r\nHe authored several best-selling books like:\r\n\r\nWings of Fire (autobiography)\r\n\r\nIgnited Minds\r\n\r\nIndia 2020\r\n\r\nThese works continue to motivate young Indians to dream big and serve the nation.', 0, '2025-06-16 16:45:32'),
